SUM.P:
We, the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service (Service), designate critical habitat for the vermilion darter (
Etheostoma chermocki
) under the Endangered Species Act of 1973, as amended (Act). We designate as critical habitat approximately 21.0 kilometers (km) (13.0 miles (mi)) of stream in 5 units within the Turkey Creek watershed in Jefferson County, AL.

